description:
Features the stories:

  1. Snipe Hunt
  2. Swamp Thing: The famed debut of Swamp Thing. Alex Olsen and Damien Ridge had been best friends, however, they both competed for the affection of a woman named Linda. Linda eventually married Alex and Damien had to endure seeing them together. Soon out of his lust for Linda, Damien conspired to eliminate Alex. He sabotaged the equipment in Alex's lab causing an explosion that killed him. Keeping the knowledge hidden from Linda, Damien buried Alex's body in the swamp. Alex came back to life, but returned as "a muck-encrusted mockery of a man." Damien eventually married the widowed Linda and they lived together in an old plantation house. Linda had never recovered from Alex's death and as the months passed, Damien began to suspect that Linda might soon learn the truth, so he prepared to kill her. The reincarnate Alex would walk around the house but this night was different. Damien, poised with a hypodermic needle ready to inject Linda, is attacked by the Swamp Thing. He breaks into the house and crushes Damien's throat. Linda flees from the creature in horror, never realizing that the monster who saved her was her beloved Alex.
  3. After I Die
  4. It's Better to Give
  5. Trick or Treat

Notes:

  • The cover is homaged by future comics.

description:
LONELY IN DEATH! Circumstances in an old house lead a young woman to believe that her recently deceased mother is attempting to kill her in order to have company in the afterlife! NEVER KILL A WITCHS SON! A niece and her husband plot to kill her uncle for insurance money, but since the uncle's mother fancies herself a witch, the husband hatches a scheme to drive his wife to suicide so that he can get all the money. Plus, THE CURSE OF THE CATS CRADLE! and THE BEAST FROM THE BOX.

Contents

  • Lonely In Death!
  • Abel's Fables From The House of Secrets (Gag page)
  • The Curse Of The Cat's Cradle (reprinted from My Greatest Adventure #85)
  • Nightmare
  • The Beast From The Box (reprinted from House of Secrets #24)
  • Never Kill A Witch's Son!

description:
A pack of child vampires decides to leave town before they are connected to local killings. They bury their coffins upon a hill until they feel that it will be safe to return to them. They row a boat out upon frigid water, intending to occupy island caves, but one drops something overboard, and the kids lose their balance and fall into the water, where they enter a torpid state. When spring comes around and the water warms up, the vampires stir and rise up during the night. They attempt to make it back to their coffins on the hill, but they discover the townspeople have paved it over with concrete in order to set up a playground devoted to their memory. As their shovels fail to penetrate the concrete, they are burned to ash as the sun rises.

Story Titles

  • Not So Loud-- I'm Blind!
  • Spawns of Satan

description:
Featuring the stories:

  1. "To Master a Mummy!" written by Scott Edelman, penciled by Charles Nicholas, inked by Romeo Tanghal, lettered by Jean Simek and colored by Jerry Serpe.
  2. "Daily Planet" Volume 78 issue 26 for the week of July 10, 1978 written by Bob Rozakis and production by Anthony Tollin.
  3. "The Smartest Plant in the World!" written by Arnold Drake, penciled and inked by Rubeny and colored by Jerry Serpe.
  4. "A Piece of the Sky" written by Bob Toomey, penciled and inked by Tom Sutton, lettered by Shelly Leferman and colored by Jerry Serpe.
  5. "The Knight in a Gilded Cage!" written by Scott Edelman, penciled and inked by Jose Luis Garcia Lopez, lettered by Todd Klein and colored by Jerry Serpe.

Notes:

  • This was the final issue in the series; House of Secrets was cancelled abruptly after this issue in the company-wide cancellation which has come to be known as the DC Implosion.
  • This issue contains the Hostess Superhero Ad, Batman, Robin and Commissioner Gordon and the "Corsair of Crime".
  • A letter to the editor from Kevin J, Dooley of Glendale, CA.
name: To Master a Mummy!; The Smartest Plant in the World!; A Piece of the Sky; The Knight in the Gilded Cage!
